Three poachers were yesterday morning gunned down by Kenya Wildlife Service officers at Mt Elgon National Park in Trans Nzoia. KWS spokesperson Paul Gathitu said officers on routine patrol encountered five poachers in the park. Two were armed. “There was an exchange of fire between the KWS team and the poachers. The two poachers who were armed managed to escape with injuries,” he said in a statement. The KWS team recovered various items used by poachers. Meanwhile, the Ol Pejeta Conservancy has received the TripAdvisor Certificate of Excellence for the seventh year in a row. The award is for organisations or destinations with consistently good visitor reviews.